{"title":"SCOR MTB drops two (or four) new mountain bikes out of BMC skunkworks","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/13/scor-mtb-fire-out-two-four-new-swiss-mountain-bikes-the-4060-and-4060-z-emtb/","date":1631545646000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13104148/scor-4060-long-travel-29er-carbon-full-suspension-mountain-bike-800x534.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs%3Adevice%2Frscb28-1\" alt=\"scor 4060 lt 29er carbon mtb swiss brand bmc group\" loading=\"eager\" srcset=\"\" sizes=\"\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\"><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-271078\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>SCOR are a new Swiss mountain bike brand, developed over the last three years by a team of engineers and riders from BMC. The brand who now sit within the BMC Group are launching with two (OK, four) mountain bikes in 2021; the SCOR 4060 and the SCOR 4060 Z eMTB. Adjustable rear wheel travel means both can run a 140mm or 160mm rear end, with a flip-chip and angle adjust headset keeping geometry in check. Here’s more.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13105319/scor-4060-seat-tube.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13105319/scor-4060-seat-tube.jpg\" alt=\"scot 4060 seat tube\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13105319/scor-4060-seat-tube.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13105319/scor-4060-seat-tube-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13105319/scor-4060-seat-tube-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13105319/scor-4060-seat-tube-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13105319/scor-4060-seat-tube-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13105319/scor-4060-seat-tube-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13105319/scor-4060-seat-tube.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13105319/scor-4060-seat-tube.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13105319/scor-4060-seat-tube-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13105319/scor-4060-seat-tube-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13105319/scor-4060-seat-tube-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13105319/scor-4060-seat-tube-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13105319/scor-4060-seat-tube-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><h2>SCOR 4060</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095318/scor-4060-carbon-mtb-tail-whip.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095318/scor-4060-carbon-mtb-tail-whip.jpg\" alt=\"scor 4060 whip\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095318/scor-4060-carbon-mtb-tail-whip.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095318/scor-4060-carbon-mtb-tail-whip-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095318/scor-4060-carbon-mtb-tail-whip-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095318/scor-4060-carbon-mtb-tail-whip-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095318/scor-4060-carbon-mtb-tail-whip-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095318/scor-4060-carbon-mtb-tail-whip-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095318/scor-4060-carbon-mtb-tail-whip.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095318/scor-4060-carbon-mtb-tail-whip.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095318/scor-4060-carbon-mtb-tail-whip-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095318/scor-4060-carbon-mtb-tail-whip-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095318/scor-4060-carbon-mtb-tail-whip-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095318/scor-4060-carbon-mtb-tail-whip-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095318/scor-4060-carbon-mtb-tail-whip-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p>The all-new SCOR 4060 is a full carbon, full suspension mountain bike. To create a bike that was sleek, with a low-slung silhouette, gravity-oriented, playful and practical, was the core aim of the SCOR team when they set out on this project three years ago.</p><p>But, they weren’t known as the “SCOR team” back then; they were made up of a small team of engineers and riders from the BMC Group. The founding members were a group of like-minded riders who wanted to create a fun, playful bike, rather than the thoroughbred race bikes BMC are better known for. Long story short, that’s exactly what they did, in their own time, using the prototyping capabilities of BMC. It seems the BMC bosses took notice, taking the SCOR brand under the BMC Group after the production of several prototypes.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13104404/scot-4060-linkage-non-drive-side.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13104404/scot-4060-linkage-non-drive-side.jpg\" alt=\"scot 4060 linkage non drive side lower link actuated virtual pivot suspension platformm\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13104404/scot-4060-linkage-non-drive-side.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13104404/scot-4060-linkage-non-drive-side-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13104404/scot-4060-linkage-non-drive-side-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13104404/scot-4060-linkage-non-drive-side-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13104404/scot-4060-linkage-non-drive-side-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13104404/scot-4060-linkage-non-drive-side-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13104404/scot-4060-linkage-non-drive-side.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13104404/scot-4060-linkage-non-drive-side.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13104404/scot-4060-linkage-non-drive-side-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13104404/scot-4060-linkage-non-drive-side-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13104404/scot-4060-linkage-non-drive-side-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13104404/scot-4060-linkage-non-drive-side-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13104404/scot-4060-linkage-non-drive-side-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p>Back to the bike. You can pick up the SCOR 4060 in a 140mm rear wheel travel (ST) or 160mm rear wheel travel (LT) configuration, each delivered by a lower-link activated virtual pivot suspension design. Switching between the two involves swapping out the shock for one with a longer stroke length, flipping the flip-chip at the lower shock mount, and adjusting the head angle with the angle-adjust headset that the bike ships with.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095322/scor-4060-lt-mtb-manual.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095322/scor-4060-lt-mtb-manual.jpg\" alt=\"scor 4060 manual\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095322/scor-4060-lt-mtb-manual.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095322/scor-4060-lt-mtb-manual-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095322/scor-4060-lt-mtb-manual-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095322/scor-4060-lt-mtb-manual-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095322/scor-4060-lt-mtb-manual-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095322/scor-4060-lt-mtb-manual-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095322/scor-4060-lt-mtb-manual.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095322/scor-4060-lt-mtb-manual.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095322/scor-4060-lt-mtb-manual-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095322/scor-4060-lt-mtb-manual-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095322/scor-4060-lt-mtb-manual-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095322/scor-4060-lt-mtb-manual-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095322/scor-4060-lt-mtb-manual-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p>Either way, the bike rolls on 29″ wheels with a thoroughly modern geometry that speaks to riders who are out to have a good time, rather than those out to race against the clock. The short 433mm chainstays are evidence of that, paired with generous reach figures that don’t push the boat out too far; that’s 435mm in small, 459mm in medium, 485mm in large and 515mm in XL. Seat tubes are nice and short too (440mm in large) allowing for the fitment of long travel dropper posts.</p><div id=\"attachment_271293\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095325/scor-4060-lt-mtb-pruple.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-271293\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095325/scor-4060-lt-mtb-pruple.jpg\" alt=\"scor 4060 head angle adjust headset\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095325/scor-4060-lt-mtb-pruple.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095325/scor-4060-lt-mtb-pruple-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095325/scor-4060-lt-mtb-pruple-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095325/scor-4060-lt-mtb-pruple-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095325/scor-4060-lt-mtb-pruple-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095325/scor-4060-lt-mtb-pruple-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095325/scor-4060-lt-mtb-pruple.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095325/scor-4060-lt-mtb-pruple.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095325/scor-4060-lt-mtb-pruple-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095325/scor-4060-lt-mtb-pruple-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095325/scor-4060-lt-mtb-pruple-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095325/scor-4060-lt-mtb-pruple-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13095325/scor-4060-lt-mtb-pruple-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-271293\">The SCOR 4060 frame is able to live with both air and coil shocks.</p></div><p>That head angle adjust headset can be used at anytime, not just when switching between long and short travel modes. In the LT config, your options are 63.8° and 65°, in-line with the steeper and more aggressive riding style you’d expect from a longer travel bike. On the ST, the head angle is slightly steeper, allowing riders to go between 64.5° and 65.5°. SCOR have provided us with complete geometry charts for both travel options, so go ahead and pore over the numbers til your heart’s content.</p><div id=\"attachment_271316\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13105405/scor-4060-st-geometry-chart.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-